<dl id="n12004m"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n12" href="#n12004m">N12 (VI.B.14)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n12all.htm#n12004m"> 4(m)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> Gargan &mdash; Tua / Gargantua</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">Passons maintenant, sans chercher aucune transition, des pygm&eacute;es aux g&eacute;ants, et en particulier &agrave; celui qui les r&eacute;sume tous: Gargantua. <font color="green">[&hellip;]</font> D&apos;apr&egrave;s une l&eacute;gende, son nom viendrait de ce que sa m&egrave;re s&apos;appelait Tua et son p&egrave;re Gargant. <br><font color="green">[Now let us go without transition from pygmies to giants and in particular to the one who epitomises them all: <mark>Gargantua</mark>.[&hellip;]</font> According to legend, his name comes from his mother who was called <mark>Tua</mark> and his father who was called <mark>Gargant</mark>.] <small> l'Abb&eacute; A. Millon, <a name="AMPB" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#AMPB"><cite title="source">Pauvres Pierres! Les Megalithes Bretons devant la science</cite></a> (n.d) 13</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
